parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight wiring harness can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Headlights burn out frequently
headlights do not turn on
headlights are dim or intermittent
wiring harness is melted or damaged
bulb replacement does not fix the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering assist fails
making it hard to turn the steering wheel

especially at low speeds; the steering wheel seizes or becomes difficult to turn; a loud whirring noise occurs while steering; the power steering pump leaks fluid; the steering wheel feels heavy or hard to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering gear fails
causing the steering wheel to become difficult to turn; a clunking noise occurs while steering; the steering wheel feels heavy or hard to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight wiring harness can cause the headlights to malfunction, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlight wiring harness melts
causing the headlights to fail; the headlights do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, and may also lead to electrical fires.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a loss of electrical power
the headlights and/or running lights fail
the air bag and traction control systems malfunction
and there may be a burning smell or smoke emanating from the electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight wiring harness can cause the headlights to fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, and may also lead to electrical fires.
symptoms: The headlights and/or running lights fail
the wiring harness is melted or damaged

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress and mold issues can cause electrical system failures, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, and may also lead to health risks for occupants.
symptoms: Water is present in the vehicle
mold is visible
and there may be a musty or mildew smell.
